<component id="ID_txt04">
<text><![CDATA[<ul><li>A firewall is network hardware or software that defines what traffic can come into and go out of sections of the network.</li><br/><li>IDS is a software- or hardware-based solution that passively listens to network traffic. It does not stop the initial traffic from passing through to the destination.</li><br/><li>IPS is an active physical device or software feature. Traffic actually passes through IPS interfaces and the IPS can block all suspicious activity in real time.</li><br/><li>A host-based firewall and Anti-X software runs directly on a host operating system and protects the host from malicious attacks that might have made it through all other layers of defense.</li></ul>]]></text>
</component>

